author: CNN
description: A federal judge in Rhode Island said Thursday that the Trump administration must fully cover food stamp benefits for tens of millions of Americans in November. “People have gone without for too long,” US District Judge John McConnell said during a hastily called hearing Thursday. “Not making payments to them for even another day is simply unacceptable.” Nearly 42 million Americans receive food stamps. Payments are made on a staggered basis over the course of a month. #CNN #News
title: Fed judge orders Trump admin to fully fund SNAP amid historic shutdown

author: CNN
description: Onita Norris is trying to figure out a problem that has no good answer. She keeps running the numbers to see how much money she has to feed her two children, both under five, and how much she’ll have to go without. CNN's Rene Marsh reports. #CNN
title: Mom struggles to feed kids as SNAP benefits lapse

author: CNN
description: Following the October 19 heist, information has resurfaced about gaps in the Louvre's security, including a claim that the password to the museum's CCTV network was at one point "Louvre." Paris Bureau Chief Saskya Vandoorne breaks it down. #cnn #news #louvre #heist
title: You’ll never guess the Louvre’s old password

author: CNN
description: Consumers are not embracing Coca-Cola's 2025 holiday commercial campaign, created completely by AI.
title: Backlash over Coca-Cola's AI Christmas Ad

author: CNN
description: Tesla shareholders on Thursday approved a compensation plan that could make CEO Elon Musk — already the world’s richest person — the first to reach trillionaire status. The company said more than 75% of votes cast supported the package at its annual shareholder meeting, excluding the roughly 15% of shares Musk already owns.      #CNN #News
title: Tesla shareholders approve Elon Musk’s potential $1 trillion compensation deal

author: CNN
description:
United Airlines will preemptively cancel about 200 flights starting Friday, the airline tells CNN. That’s roughly 4% of United’s Friday schedule and is comprised of mostly regional flights. United says it will cancel about 4% again on Saturday and Sunday. The announcement from United came as the Trump administration is considering a 4% reduction in flights starting tomorrow, an airline official familiar with the proposal told CNN. The proposal is preliminary and nothing is final, a separate source said.
 #CNN #News
title: United, Delta cancel flights as nation braces for FAA cuts

author: CNN
description: The US Department of Agriculture on Wednesday evening issued updated guidance that will allow food stamp recipients to receive slightly higher partial benefits in November. According to a new court filing, the USDA will now cut the maximum Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program benefit by 35%—less than the originally planned 50% reduction.    #CNN #News
title: USDA eases SNAP cuts, allowing larger partial benefits in November

author: CNN
description: Kremlin spokesperson Dmitry Peskov told CNN that Russia is "investigating whether it is necessary to start preparations" for nuclear testing. CNN senior correspondent Fred Pleitgen explains what this could mean. #cnn #news #russia #putin
title: Putin considers nuclear testing prep

author: CNN
description: CNN Creators discuss the role of AI in sport and whether new apps will replace the way we train, plus should we be using navigation apps less?  #CNN #News
title: Are we losing traditional skills to tech?

author: CNN
description: The Trump administration announced deals that will lower the prices of major obesity drugs for many Americans. Under the deals with Eli Lilly and Novo Nordisk, those buying injectable GLP-1 medications directly from the companies will pay an average of $350 per month, but the drugmakers have committed to reducing the price to around $250 over the next two years, according to senior administration officials. If oral GLP-1 tablets are approved by the US Food and Drug Administration, the lowest dose will cost $149. #cnn #news #ozempic #wegovy #trump
title: Trump announces price cuts to weight loss drugs

author: CNN

title: Marjorie Taylor Greene responds to AOC’s 'revenge tour' claim

description:
A massive fire engulfed the home of Miami Heat head coach Erik Spoelstra, CNN affiliate WSVN reports. According to officials, no one was injured. CNN has reached out to the Miami Heat and Spoelstra for comment.

#cnn #news #miami #fire
title: Fire reportedly burns Miami Heat head coach's home

title: Jury awards $10 million to VA teacher shot by student
